      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i think i found a leak in our order processing module. the profiting looks weird after a few hours of uptime. i'm looking at this block where we handle the limit orders. can u tell me why this is leaking memory and how i should use smart pointers to fix it?\n\n```cpp\nvoid processOrder(Order* order) {\n    if (order->isValid()) {\n        // logic for high freq execution\n        executeTrade(order);\n    }\n    // i might be forgetting something here?\n}\n\n// in the main loop\nOrder* newOrder = new Order(data);\nprocessOrder(newOrder);\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
